{"lemma":"نُهُرِ","slug":"نُهُرِ","root":"ن.ه.ر","root_slug":"ن-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَهار","root":"نهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":57},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40631","n40633","n40634","n40635"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%87%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"daytime, day","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chick of a bustard (حُبَارَى (ḥubārā)), curlew (كَرَوَان (karawān)), sandgrouse (قَطًا (qaṭan)) and/or owl (بُوم (būm))","tags":["countable","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cock of a bustard or owl","tags":["countable","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"possibly related to Aramaic נְהַר."},"ipa":["/na.haːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40631","headword_ar":"نَهَرَ","root":"nhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along, the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made for itself a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahor","text_ar":"نَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel like that of a river"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) See also 10. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything, as in one copy of the S, or anything copious, as in another copy of the S and in the TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astnhr","text_ar":"استنهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anthr","text_ar":"انتهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(blood)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed with force:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2858},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohara","text_ar":"اَنْهَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(blood)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a river:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the latter also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a vein)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed and would not stop;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it flowed like a river;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anthr","text_ar":"انتهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh, K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anhr","text_ar":"انهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same said of the belly; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the belly)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became loose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relaxed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it discharged itself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anthr","text_ar":"انتهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahara","text_ar":"نَهَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K.) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dug"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahor","text_ar":"نَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or channel for a river]: (S, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahor","text_ar":"نَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or river]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahra","text_ar":"نَهرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made an inroad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incursion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inroads"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incursions, into the territory"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"territories of enemies, in the day-time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharahu","text_ar":"نَهَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anthrhu","text_ar":"انتهرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He chid him; he checked him, restrained him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbade him, with rough speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zajarahu","text_ar":"زَجَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K, and so in a copy of the S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabarahu","text_ar":"زَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in another copy of the S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikalaAmK galiyZK","text_ar":"بِكَلَامٍ غَلِيظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be addressed him with chiding speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbidding him from doing evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK. [in the TA, citing the last explanation from the T,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano xayorK","text_ar":"عَنْ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano $ar~K","text_ar":"عَنْ شَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) It is said in the Kur, [xciii. 10,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^am~aA A@ls~aAy^ila falaA tanoharo","text_ar":"وَاَمَّا ا@لسَّايِلَ فَلَا تَنْهَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And as for the beggar, thou shalt not chide"},{"kind":"text","text":"him, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"address"},{"kind":"text","text":"him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with rough speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mani A@notahara","text_ar":"مَنِ ا@نْتَهَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHiba bidoEapK malaA^a A@ll~`hu qalobahu A^amonFA wiA_iymaAnFA waA^am~anahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"صَاحِبَ بِدْعَةٍ مَلَاَ ا@للّٰهُ قَلْبَهُ اَمْنًا وِاـِيمَانًا وَاَمَّنَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlfazaEi A@loA^akobar","text_ar":"مِنَ الفَزَعِ ا@لْاَكْبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso chideth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"checketh with rough speech, the author of an innovation in religion, God will fill his heart with security and faith, and God will preserve him from the greatest terror"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","K","Sgh","Mgh","JK","A"]},{"entry_id":"n40633","headword_ar":"نَهْرٌ","root":"nhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel in which water runs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) so most say: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a river; a rivulet; a brook; a canal of running water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wide channel in which water runs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) or properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide running water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and by a secondary application, which is tropical. (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trench"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which it runs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA *:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohurN","text_ar":"اَنْهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) a pl. of the former, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohaArN","text_ar":"اَنْهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) a pl. of the latter, (Msb,) [but used as a pl. of either, both of pauc. and of mult. and the most common of all the pls.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhurN","text_ar":"نُهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, and so in some copies of the K,) with two dammehs, a pl. of the former, (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhorN","text_ar":"نُهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K and in the TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhuwrN","text_ar":"نُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY","text_ar":"جَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ahoru","text_ar":"النَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The river ran,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY AlmiyzaAbu","text_ar":"جَرَى المِيزَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN kaviyr AlmaA='i","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ كَثِير المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel of running water having much water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in a pl. sense: as in the Kur, [liv. 54],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY jan~aAtK wanaharK","text_ar":"فِى جَنَّاتٍ وَنَهَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In gardens and"},{"kind":"text","text":"among"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivers"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohaAri","text_ar":"اَنْهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like the phrase in the Kur, (same chap. verse 45,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayuwal~uwna Ald~ubora","text_ar":"وَيُوَلُّونَ الدُّبْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S.) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^adobaAra","text_ar":"الاَدْبَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, TA:) but it is otherwise explained. (S.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naharN","text_ar":"نَهَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n40634","headword_ar":"نَهَرٌ","root":"nhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Amplitude:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light and amplitude:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so, accord. to some, in the Kur, liv. 54, differently explained above: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahorN","text_ar":"نَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA.) or, accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahar","text_ar":"نَهَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. [or rather quasi pl.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhurN","text_ar":"نُهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhaArN","text_ar":"نهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n40635","headword_ar":"نَهِرٌ","root":"nhr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahyrN","text_ar":"نَهيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) both applied to water. (TA.) ―         -b2-  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahor","text_ar":"نَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or river, or channel in which water runs]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxulN nahirN","text_ar":"رَخُلٌ نَهِرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of day-time"},{"kind":"text","text":"; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibu nahaArK","text_ar":"صَاحِبُ نَهَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes inroads or incursions into the territories of enemies therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who works therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) a kind of rel. n.; as is shown by the ex."},{"kind":"quote","text":"lasotu bilayoliY~K wal`kin~iY nhirN\n                      \n                     \n                        laA A^udoliju All~ayola wal`kino A^abotakiro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am not one of the night-time, but I am one of the day-time; I do not journey in the night, but I go forth early in the morning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: as though he said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaAriY~","text_ar":"نَهَارِىّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb.) The verse is correctly related as above; not as it is given in the S. (IB.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoharu","text_ar":"اَنْهَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}